==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hushed
<hw>hushed</hw> <pr>(h⟦ucr⟧sht)</pr>, <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>having the sound level reduced; -- especially used of the noise of
conversation; <as>as, speaking in <ex>hushed</ex> tones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> muted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having relatively little noise; <as>as, a
<ex>hushed</ex> church</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> quiet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hushed-up</ent>⟦br⟧
